  "text": "Fine-tuned the sweatband stripe positioning after user feedback. The key was finding the sweet spot between too small (when I shortened it too much) and overlapping the stroke (original size). The 75% adjustment back from the over-shortened version gave the perfect balance - visible colored stripe with just enough margin from the black stroke edges. \n\nAlso successfully removed the problematic light color (#F7CF47 - MANGO) from the sweatband color array while keeping the other bright colors that have good contrast against the white background.",
